label: 'dul ba cha [17th century]
description: The volume contains Vinaya texts on discipline in the Sarvastivada school. The Vinaya corpus deals with the topic of monastic discipline and stories and anecdotes from the time of the Buddha. The stories constitute the contextual narrative for the various rules and precepts to be observed by the monks and the explanation for life experiences and events through karmic connection to the past lifetimes.
